**Why this matters:**
- FontAwesome processes icons when the page loads
- Adding **any** custom/BEM class on the same `<i>` as the FontAwesome classes (e.g. `ubits-checkbox__check`, `ubits-status-tag__icon`) can **break icon rendering** (icon no se carga). Aplica tanto a HTML estático como a `innerHTML`.
- **Solution:** Use **only** FontAwesome classes on the `<i>` tag: `far fa-check` or `fas fa-*`. **No** añadir clases propias del componente en el `<i>`.
- **Styling:** Apply size/color via CSS **parent selector** (e.g. `.ubits-checkbox__box i`, `.ubits-status-tag i`), never via a class on the `<i>`.
- **Checkbox:** El check debe ser `<i class="far fa-check"></i>` dentro de `.ubits-checkbox__box`, sin clase `ubits-checkbox__check`; estilos en `.ubits-checkbox__box i`.
- **Reference:** See `button.html` line 619 for dynamic: `<i class="far fa-${icon}"></i>`; see `checkbox.css` and `badge-tag.css` for parent-selector styling.

**Common icon classes:**
- `far fa-check` - Check mark
- `far fa-times` - X mark  
- `far fa-plus` - Plus sign
- `far fa-home` - Home icon
- `far fa-user` - User icon

